<file path="README.md">
# h-graphic-generator

CLI and MCP server for generating branded graphics and diagrams.

## Features

- **Dual Renderer**: Satori (fast, simple CSS) + Puppeteer (full CSS support)
- **MCP Server**: Integration with Claude Desktop for AI-assisted graphic generation
- **Template System**: Pre-built templates for common graphic types
- **Brand Tokens**: Consistent styling across all outputs
- **Multiple Formats**: SVG, PNG, JPG, WebP output

## Installation

```bash
npm install
npm run build
```

## Usage

### CLI

```bash
# Generate graphic from template
hgraphic generate --template feature-illustration --props '{"title":"Hello"}' --output out.png

# List available templates
hgraphic templates list

# Validate brand config
hgraphic brand validate
```

### MCP Server (Claude Desktop)

Add to your Claude Desktop config:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "h-graphic-generator": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/dist/mcp/server.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Brand Configuration

Create `brand/brand.json` with your brand tokens:

```json
{
  "$schema": "h-graphic-brand-v1",
  "name": "My Brand",
  "colors": {
    "primary": { "value": "#0066CC" },
    "secondary": { "value": "#FF6B35" },
    "background": { "value": "#FFFFFF" },
    "text": { "value": "#1A1A2E" }
  },
  "typography": {
    "display": { "family": "Inter", "weight": "700" },
    "heading": { "family": "Inter", "weight": "600" },
    "body": { "family": "Inter", "weight": "400" }
  }
}
```

## Development

```bash
npm run dev      # Watch mode
npm run test     # Run tests
npm run lint     # Lint code
```

## License

MIT
